   Pretrial Services Reporting Instructions

   In Indianapolis, the Pretrial Services Office is located at:

     Room 101, U.S. Courthouse
     46 East Ohio Street
     Indianapolis, IN  46204
     (317) 229-3750.
     Recorder for telephone reporting:  (317) 229-3766.

   If you are to report to a divisional office, click here for district
   office addresses and phone numbers.

   Individual reporting instructions are provided by the Pretrial Services
   Officer to each released client.  However, all pretrial clients must
   notify their Pretrial Services Officer immediately of any change in
   address, telephone, or employment.

   Pretrial clients shall not commit a federal, state, or local crime
   during their period of release.  Clients shall information the Pretrial
   Services or Probation Officer immediately if charged with any offense.

   Failure to comply with the Court-ordered pretrial reporting
   instructions will be reported to the Court and may result in the
   revocation of bond and detention pending case outcome.
